		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Model-driven architecture</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Model-driven architecture</b> (MDA) is a <a href="/wiki/Software_design" title="Software design">software design</a> approach for the development of <a href="/wiki/Software_system" title="Software system">software systems</a>. It provides a set of guidelines for the structuring of specifications, which are expressed as <a href="/wiki/Computer_model" title="Computer model" class="mw-redirect">models</a>. Model-driven architecture is a kind of <a href="/wiki/Domain_engineering" title="Domain engineering">domain engineering</a>, and supports <a href="/wiki/Model-driven_engineering" title="Model-driven engineering">model-driven engineering</a> of software systems. It was launched by the <a href="/wiki/Object_Management_Group" title="Object Management Group">Object Management Group</a> (OMG) in 2001.<sup id="cite_ref-proposal_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-proposal-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
